         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">20/2/82 ¶  ¶ In my letter about the plants that you collected with Professor Tate southeast from there, I had named the  ¶ Cyperus ¶  as  ¶ C. gracilis ¶  simply from the appearance. This shows again ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">82.02.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply with parcel 6.3.82'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>20/2/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In meinem Briefe über die Pflanzen, welche Sie südöstlich von dort mit Prof. Tate sammelten, hatte ich den Cyperus als C. gracilis bennent einfach nach dem Ansehen. Dies zeigt wieder, dass man nicht übereilt verfahren sollte, im Benennen von Pflanzen, lieber Herr Tepper, denn bei genauerer Untersuchung stellt es sich heraus, dass es C. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">tenellus</hi>
               </seg>, L. fil. ist. Beide Arten sind nahe verwandt; übrigens ist C. gracilis auch in S.A., nämlich am <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Lake Eyre.</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wie oft publicirt die Adelaider Königl Gesellschaft? u bekommt der Autor gleich nach dem Druck der Abhandlung seine Extra-Abdrücke?</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit bestem Grusse</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/2/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In my letter about the plants that you collected with Professor Tate southeast from there, I had named the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cyperus</seg> as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. gracilis</seg> simply from the appearance. This shows again that one should not act hastily in the naming of plants, dear Mr Tepper, because on a more detailed investigation it turns out that it is <seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <hi rend="underline">tenellus</hi>
               </seg> L. fil. Both species are closely related; by the way <seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. gracilis</seg> is also in South Australia, namely at <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Lake Eyre</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>How often does the Adelaide Royal Society publish and does the author receive his extra reprints right after the printing of the paper?</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With best greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cyperus%20gracilis">Cyperus gracilis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Cyperus</seg>
               <seg style="">tenellus</seg>
            </p>
